title: Grateful Dead Live at Cumberland County Civic Center on 1982-09-17
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi CR-5A > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab 2448 > CD-Wave (24bit output) > TLH > FLAC 2448 tagged. Transferred by Andrew F. 03/2016
description:
Set 1

Bertha-> Promised Land, Candyman-> CC Rider, Althea, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Dupree's Diamond Blues, It's All Over Now, West L.A. Fadeaway, Throwing Stones, Deal

Set 2

Touch Of Gray-> Women Are Smarter, High Time, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Spanish Jam-> The Other One-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Morning Dew-> Sugar Magnolia, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
So good This show was so good then and still is now. You did an outstanding job recording and uploading this one. Anyone in the know new this show is rock solid from start to finish. The sound is off the charts. I say it every time thank you thank thank you. 
 Wavy Gravy would say ' these are the good old days'........

The eve before my first show I would see the GD for the first time on 9/18/82. A holy experience in the true sense of the word.

A little later, when I started acquiring bootleg tapes (I know, not bootlegs in context of GD), I got the tape of this show 9/17/82 from this exact recording.

This Cumberland show is exceptional and the audience recording puts you right there. One of the best GD show recordings I’ve ever heard because of its transportation power.

The show is awesome too. That Bertha. High Time. Touch of Grey. And the GDTRFB>Morning Dew.

I thank the boys and the universe for this show.
